# Force LF in the working tree on every platform. The lexer/snapshot fixtures
# are byte-offset sensitive, so a CRLF checkout (GitHub's Windows runners default
# to core.autocrlf=true) shifts every offset and fails the snapshot tests. This
# keeps Windows checkouts identical to Linux.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply line-ending conversion.
*.bmp binary
*.wav binary
*.til binary
